This paper is about multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL), which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper discusses various algorithms and theoretical frameworks for MARL, which are relevant to the subcategories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses game theory and decision-making, which are relevant to the subcategories of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Therefore, the most likely subcategories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.MA, and cs.SY, in that order.
